                            <comment id="16226449" author="arturocandela" created="Tue, 31 Oct 2017 08:25:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=JSteward&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;JSteward&quot;&gt;Josh Steward&lt;/a&gt; reoported, There are problems when the Avro generated c# classes are in another dll Library instead of beeing in the &quot;.exe&quot; project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;My group is currently developing a project that includes a lot of shared objects and I&apos;m developing a Project Library (dll) that includes all the generated objects between all the applications.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem that I&apos;m having with this model is that a nested object cannot be deserialized because It fails. If the object is simple, It can be deserialized without problems. But if I put the generated objects in the &quot;.exe&quot; Project, it works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to look if I&apos;m able to pass to avro in which dll are the object definitions so avro will be able to deserialize the objects. I find something I will add to this bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regard.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
